sentence: Comparing units outstanding versus one week ago at the coverage universe of ETFs at ETF Channel, the biggest inflow was seen in The Consumer Staples Select Sector SPDR Fund (XLP), which added 11,500,000 units, or a 5.6% increase week over week.
Among the largest underlying components of XLP, in morning trading today Procter & Gamble Company (PG) is up about 0.5%, and Coca-Cola Company (KO) is lower by about 0.1%.
And on a percentage change basis, the ETF with the biggest increase in inflows was the IBMO ETF (IBMO), which added 100,000 units, for a 40.0% increase in outstanding units.
